  "doc_id": "19409",
  "text": "The birth weight charts for US babies with Down syndrome derived by [CITATION_1] gave similar results to ours (e.g., at 38 weeks gestation median birth weight for boys was 3,048 g vs. 2,947 g in this study and for girls 3,092 g vs. 3,019 g). Median birth weight for unaffected babies is greater in North America than England and Wales, so a larger difference might have been expected. Against that, Boghossian only included babies admitted to hospital at birth or dying before admission; this might be expected to be a \"sicker\" population, biasing the weight centiles downwards, which might explain why the differences between the studies were small.",
  "correct_citation": {
